    <content>&lt;P&gt;Hi all&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;We are on S/4 HANA Public Cloud 2408. I would like to understand how MRP rescheduling works in Public Cloud and how it is different from S/4 private cloud/On-Prem.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;MRP seems to generate redundant purchase requisitions. I have looked at SAP Note&amp;nbsp;1745312 - MRP creates redundant proposals though there are fixed future receipts which can cover the requirements. And the behaviour is different. Can someone explain if there are differences in behaviour in Public Cloud?&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;The material master has Planning Strategy 10, Planned Delivery Time = 0, Goods Receipt Time=2 days, Lot&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;Sizing = MB with min lot size 1200. There is a Purchase Info Record with Auto. Sourcing Flag and it has Planned Delivery Time = 210 days and GRT=2 days. The Plant config has a rescheduling horizon of 100 days and tolerance of 2 says. Both MD04 and Monitor/Manage Material Coverage App show PDT=0, GRT=2 and Total RLT=0.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;MRP run today (25/10/2024) has generated a redundant requisition. See MRP output below. The Purchase Req is highlighted in bold. I have tried deleting the Req and also running MRP with Regen.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;Your help will be much appreciated.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;TABLE width="780px"&gt;&lt;TBODY&gt;&lt;TR&gt;&lt;TD width="91.0781px"&gt;Date&lt;/TD&gt;&lt;TD width="161.688px"&gt;MRP Element&lt;/TD&gt;&lt;TD width="121.781px"&gt;Additional Info&lt;/TD&gt;&lt;TD width="237.531px"&gt;Issue 1&lt;/TD&gt;&lt;TD width="80.9375px"&gt;Quantity&lt;/TD&gt;&lt;TD width="85.9844px"&gt;Available&lt;/TD&gt;&lt;/TR&gt;&lt;TR&gt;&lt;TD width="91.0781px"&gt;25.10.2024&lt;/TD&gt;&lt;TD width="161.688px"&gt;Stock&lt;/TD&gt;&lt;TD width="121.781px"&gt;No Safety Stock&lt;/TD&gt;&lt;TD width="237.531px"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/TD&gt;&lt;TD width="80.9375px"&gt;1176 PC&lt;/TD&gt;&lt;TD width="85.9844px"&gt;1176 PC&lt;/TD&gt;&lt;/TR&gt;&lt;TR&gt;&lt;TD width="91.0781px"&gt;2